    "en": {
      "title": "PM\u2019s plan on debt also impossible: Harsha",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Opposition Parliamentarian Dr. Harsha de Silva says that it is not possible to restructure the country\u2019s debts by August, despite the Prime Minister\u2019s assurances.",
        "The Samagi Jana Balawegaya MP, citing the Prime Minister\u2019s speech with regard to the IMF debt restructuring, stated that although Prime Minister himself said that if the plan presented by NPP Leader Anura Kumara Dissanayake to revitalize the country\u2019s economy within six months\u2019 time is impractical, the plan presented by the Prime Minister himself is one which might end up in the Book of Guinness World Records if achieved.",
        "\u201cThere are only\u00a0three weeks left in August. I am not confident that this loan can be restructured in three weeks,\u201d he added."
      ],
